  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/chlimage_1-36.png" /> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/dc_chart_use.png" /> 
  <note> 
   <p>You can create a custom AEM chart control that displays data located in the AEM JCR. For information, see <a href="/content/help/en/experience-manager/using/displaying-experience-manager-data-chart">Displaying Adobe Experience Manager Data in a Chart</a>.</p> 
  </note> 
  <h3>Content Fragment</h3> 
  <note> 
   <p>The full functionality of Content Fragment Management is only available with the touch-optimized UI.</p> 
   <p>The Content Fragment component can be seen in the classic UI sidekick, but further functions are not available.</p> 
  </note> 
  <p><a href="../../../sites/classic-ui-authoring/using/classic-page-author-content-fragments.md">Content fragments</a> are created and managed as page-independent assets. You can then use these fragments, and their variations, when authoring your content pages.</p> 
