  <h3>External</h3> 
  <p>The external application integration component (<strong>External</strong>) enables you to embed external applications into your AEM page using an iframe.<br /> </p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong>External</strong> 
    <ul> 
     <li><strong>Target application</strong><br /> Specify the URL of the web application to be integrated; for example:<br /> <code class="code"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page
       <discoiqbr /> </code></li> 
     <li><strong>Pass parameters</strong><br /> Check the box for parameters to be passed to the application when required.</li> 
     <li><strong>Width and Height<br /> </strong>Define the size of the iframe</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> 
  <p>The external application is integrated into the paragraph system of the AEM page; for example, when using a Target application of <span class="code">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page</span>:</p> 
