  <h3>Slideshow</h3> 
  <p>This component allows you to load a series of images to be displayed as a slideshow on your page.You can add or remove images and assign each a title. Under Advanced you can also specify the size of the display area.</p> 
  <p>You can configure:</p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong>Slides</strong> 
    <ul> 
     <li><strong>New Slide</strong><br /> You can specify a selection of slides using the <strong>Add</strong> (and <strong>Remove</strong>) buttons.<br /> </li> 
     <li><strong>Title</strong><br /> Specify a title if required. This is overlaid on the appropriate slide.</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
   <li><strong>Advanced</strong> 
    <ul> 
     <li><strong>Size</strong><br /> Specify the width and height in pixels.<br /> </li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> 
  <p>The slideshow component then repeatedly displays each in sequence, for a short period of time, before fading through to the next slide:</p> 
  <img imageRotate="0" src="assets/dc_slideshow_use.png" /> 
